    "At this point, we mention the controversy in the literature about the evidence that there are real out-of-sample benefits to investors when relay on predictive models (Welch and Goyal, 2007; Johannes et al., 2014).",
    "ML methods, with their high-dimensional nature, encompass diverse techniques, from traditional statistical learning methods like Gradient-Boosted Trees and Random Forest (RF) to the latest and popular algorithms such as Deep Learning (DL) or Deep Neural Networks (DNN).",
    "These methods use learning algorithms to identify the best-performing assets based on profitability and risk for a specific period.",
    "The goal of all of these methods is to approximate best the conditional expectation E(r i,t+1 |F t), where r i,t+1 is an asset's return over the risk-free, and F t is the actual and observable information set of market participants.",
    "Portfolio efficiency, gauged in profitability, is enhanced when assets are preselected based on return predictability, with the prominent application of ML techniques (Ballings et al., 2015; Kaczmarek and Perez, 2021)."
